Given the uncertainties and challenges we're facing, we've launched a fundraising campaign to provide for unmet needs that may come up as we begin school this fall. These needs range from basics, like food, to school-specific needs, like hand sanitizer stations and signage, to learning needs, like Chromebooks and access to the Internet. Our BPE board and generous donors have pledged to match the first $20,000 we raise! Please consider a donation towards our goal of $20,000 per school, $40,000 in total.

https://donorbox.org/dudley-education-fund

Dudley Street Neighborhood Charter School added 10 new photos.
January 19, 2016 at 5:05 PM ·

The Dudley Street Neighborhood Charter School hosted Martin Luther King Learning Day on Monday in honor of Dr. King's legacy. Residents from the Boston Teacher Residency and corps members from the Dudley Promise Corps led art projects, read alouds, and screened the movie "Our Friend, Martin" in a day of service. The day provided our scholars and families opportunities to learn about and celebrate the legacy of MLK Jr. and the civil rights movement. Thank you Dudley Promise Corps for organizing this wonderful event!
